-=-=-=-=-=-=-=- My Vision Of Castles -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                        -or-
-=-=-=-=-=-=-= My Kingdom For A Horse =-=-=-=-=-=-=-

1) Environs

a) Should be specially prepared sites (ie. this area looks suitable for a castle)
b) Various topographies: forested, plains, mountainous, etc.
	 i) terrain governs foodstuffs, wood, mining
	ii) terrain governs defense
c) Should be a 20x20(?) grid around the castle for taxes, food production, wars
d) Should include a town and a castle
e) Various benefits/detriments based on continent


2) Economy

a) Inhabitants are taxed.
b) Stores and the like can be located in towns/keeps
c) NPC inhabitants slowly accrue over time depending on tax and factors in 1)
d) PC inhabitants make their own decisions. :-)
e) Kingdom city starts out as a few huts.
f) Kingdoms can commission uniques or Wonders.


3) Castle

a) Each room must be bought and built (which takes time).
b) Rooms include:
	  i) Castle walls, of various materials, size, and strength
	 ii) Specialty defense: barbican, drawbridge, etc.
	iii) Interior rooms (market place, stables, bunkhouses, etc)
	 iv) Keep rooms (throne rooms, banquet, sleeping, etc)
c) The bigger the castle, the better the morale of the kingdom inhabitants
d) Castles can also be things like strongholds (think of a thief king stronghold in the forest)
e) Materials: wood, stone, steel, "wizard's stone" (requires a Mage to create)
f) Castles can be built within a kingdom by allowed nobility of that kingdom, which extends the influence and boundaries of that kingdom.


4) Wars

a) Kingdom can hire guards and militia
	  i) Patrols
	 ii) Keep guards
	iii) Companies of archers
	 iv) Infantry
	  v) Cavalry - uses a modified Paladin warhorse
	 vi) Mountain/forest/desert units
b) Militia treated as group NPCs, ie. "a company of archers (5)"
c) Siege engines can be employed to damage or defend the castle
	  i) hard to get catapults into the mountains, etc.
	 ii) vehicle based "covered gate ram"
	iii) oil, fire, etc.
d) The Engineer's Guild
	  i) Players can design/create siege weapons
	 ii) Players can "size up" opponent castles (wall height, etc) from afar
	iii) Players can research technology
e) When hiring militia, the kingdom can announce that it is hiring. Militia will then trickle in. This is to avoid a situation where people hire militia just before a war and then dismiss them all immediately afterwards.


